#: ../../../src/config/intro.rst:108
msgid "For example::"
msgstr ""

# 25537dadaeb741a3b48caa5b20cf90c2
#: ../../../src/config/intro.rst:114
msgid "Each configuration file line may contains `section` definition, `parameter` specification, empty (space and newline characters only) or `commented` line. You can setup `inline` commentaries for `sections` or `parameters`."
msgstr ""

# cd2477b141f5416da120832d7ec687c1
#: ../../../src/config/intro.rst:118
msgid "The `section` defines group of parameters that are belongs to some specific CouchDB subsystem. For instance, :section:`httpd` section holds not only HTTP server parameters, but also others that directly interacts with it."
msgstr ""

# 085970dea628447089e318649c74ddd7
#: ../../../src/config/intro.rst:122
msgid "The `parameter` specification contains two parts divided by the `equal` sign (``=``): the parameter name on the left side and the parameter value on the right one. The leading and following whitespace for ``=`` is an optional to improve configuration readability."
msgstr ""

# 74b65a3930584380af3a279be44221a6
#: ../../../src/config/intro.rst:128
msgid "In case when you'd like to remove some parameter from the `default.ini` without his modification, you may specify him within the `local.ini`, but without any value::"
msgstr ""

